[REQUIRED]
# Deliverables
- Annotated source code of the website
- Planning documentation for each user story

[ACCESS: PUBLIC (Without login)]
- [x] Login with username & password
- [x] Registration / create new user account

[ACCESS: AUTHENTICATED (Logged-in users)]
- [x] Logout
- [x] Simple welcome page
- [x] List own stations
    - [x] Edit station name
    - [x] Edit station description
- [x] Register unassigned station by serial number
- [x] Edit own user account
    - username, password, email, first name, last name
- [] View measurement data from own stations
    - filter by date/time
- [] Friend management
    - add users as friends
    - display friends
    - end friendships
- [] Collections
    - add measurement data to collections (only from own stations)
    - collection = (station, start datetime, end datetime)
    - rename own collections
    - delete own collections
    - share collections with friends
    - undo sharing
    - view collections shared with you

[ACCESS: ADMIN (additional)]
- [] Edit / delete any user account
- [] Assign admin rights
- [] Create new user accounts
- [] Edit / delete any station
- [] Create new stations
- [] View/filter/delete measurement data from all stations (by date/time)
- [] Add measurement data from all stations to collections
- [] Rename / delete any collection
- Note: Admins may only share collections they created themselves

[SHOULD]
- [] Welcome dashboard showing current measurements from own stations
- [] Appealing, user-friendly design (UX)
- [] Validate user inputs
- [] Friend requests require confirmation (no direct adds)
- [] When friendship ends, automatically unshare collections between the two users

[COULD - Nice to have]
- [] Register stations via QR code
- [] Display measurement data with diagrams / charts
- [] Responsive design (adapt to screen sizes)
- [] Themes (light/dark) persistent after logout
- [] Multi-language support persistent after logout
- [] Notifications / emails for events (friend requests, shares, errors)
- [] User-to-user chat
- [] Invite links to onboard new users